{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2687"},"text":"section 2687 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 2905 of the Defense Base Closure and Realignment Act of 1990, referred to in subsec. (a)(1)(C), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/510/s2905"},"text":"section 2905 of Pub. L. 101–510","children":[],"tail":", which is set out in a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2687"},"text":"section 2687 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcc563622-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/254"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–254","children":[],"tail":" added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/95/s146/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–95, § 146(a)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/95/s146/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–95, § 146(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Airports” for “Airport” in heading and “3 of the airports bearing designations under subsection (a) may be general aviation airports that were former military installations” for “one of the airports bearing a designation under subsection (a) may be a general aviation airport that was a former military installation” in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/95/s146/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–95, § 146(c)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (h)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/176/s153/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–176, § 153(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “From amounts the Secretary distributes to an airport under section 47115, $10,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2004 and 2005, and $7,000,000 for each fiscal year thereafter, is available” for “Not more than $7,000,000 for each airport from amounts the Secretary distributes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s47115"},"text":"section 47115 of this title","children":[],"tail":" for a fiscal year is available” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/176/s153/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–176, § 153(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), inserted par. (1) designation and heading, substituted “From amounts the Secretary distributes to an airport under section 47115, $10,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2004 and 2005, and $7,000,000 for each fiscal year thereafter, is available” for “Not more than a total of $7,000,000 for each airport from amounts the Secretary distributes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s47115"},"text":"section 47115 of this title","children":[],"tail":" for fiscal years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1992","children":[],"tail":", is available”, and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s130/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181, § 130(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “15” for “12” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s130/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181, § 130(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (2) and struck out former par. (2) which read as follows: “the Secretary finds that such grants would—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) reduce delays at an airport with more than 20,000 hours of annual delays in commercial passenger aircraft takeoffs and landings; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) enhance airport and air traffic control system capacity in a metropolitan area or reduce current and projected flight delays.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s130/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181, § 130(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c) and struck out heading and text of former subsec. (c). Text read as follows: “In carrying out this section, the Secretary shall consider only current or former military airports that, when at least partly converted to civilian commercial or reliever airports as part of the national air transportation system, will enhance airport and air traffic control system capacity in major metropolitan areas and reduce current and projected flight delays.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s130/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181, § 130(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “47117(e)(1)(B)” for “47117(e)(1)(E)”, “periods, each not to exceed 5 fiscal years,” for “5-fiscal-year periods”, and “each such subsequent period” for “each such subsequent 5-fiscal-year period”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s130/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181, § 130(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “$7,000,000” for “$5,000,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s130/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181, § 130(c)","children":[],"tail":", in heading, substituted “Hangars, and Air Cargo Terminals” for “and Hangars” and, in text, substituted “$7,000,000” for “$4,000,000” and inserted “and air cargo terminals of an area that is 50,000 square feet or less” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s130/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181, § 130(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (g)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287/s5/83/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287, § 5(83)(A)","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of subsec. (a) by substituting “before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-08-24"},"text":"August 24, 1994","children":[],"tail":"” for “on or before the date of the enactment of this sentence”, could not be executed because the phrase to be amended did not appear subsequent to amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/s124/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–264, § 124(a)","children":[],"tail":". See below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/s124/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–264, § 124(a)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (a) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (a) read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(a) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"General Requirements","children":[],"tail":".—The Secretary of Transportation shall designate not more than 15 current or former military airports for which grants may be made under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s47117/e/1/E"},"text":"section 47117(e)(1)(E) of this title","children":[],"tail":". The Secretary may only designate an airport for such grants (other than an airport designated for such grants on or before the date of the enactment of this sentence) if the Secretary finds that grants under such section for projects at such airport would reduce delays at an airport with more than 20,000 hours of annual delays in commercial passenger aircraft takeoffs and landings.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/s124/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–264, § 124(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “designation, and for subsequent 5-fiscal-year periods if the Secretary determines that the airport satisfies the designation criteria under subsection (a) at the beginning of each such subsequent 5-fiscal-year period.” for “designation.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287/s5/83/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287, § 5(83)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Not” for “Notwithstanding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s47109/c"},"text":"section 47109(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":", not”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/264/s124/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–264, § 124(c)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (f) by substituting “Utilities, and Hangars” for “and Utilities” in heading and “for fiscal years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1992","children":[],"tail":",” for “for the fiscal years ending "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1993","children":[],"tail":"–1996,” and “utilities, and hangars” for “and utilities” in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/305/s116/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–305, § 116(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “15” for “12” and inserted at end “The Secretary may only designate an airport for such grants (other than an airport designated for such grants on or before the date of the enactment of this sentence) if the Secretary finds that grants under such section for projects at such airport would reduce delays at an airport with more than 20,000 hours of annual delays in commercial passenger aircraft takeoffs and landings.”"}],"tail":"